    "body": "cc @luukvbaal \r\n\r\n(I might need to update https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/34281 .)\r\n\r\nIt is clear now that errors show never popup beyond 'cmdheight'. Ever. ",
    "closed_at": null,
    "comment_data": [],
    "comment_regular_data": [
        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "> It is clear now that errors show never popup beyond 'cmdheight'. Ever.\r\n\r\nCan you elaborate how this became clear? I tend to agree but I think you previously argued that routing based on message kind is unpredictable, which prompted #35028. There is merit to that sentiment, and this may be solved by the `kind:route` mapping option instead? Leaving the default \"predictable\". \r\n\r\nThough if we can single out and document some kinds it can still be predictable of course. Just curious for your reasoning here since you were against it previously.",
            "created_at": "2025-10-16T12:32:31Z",
            "html_url": "https://github.com/neovim/neovim/pull/36188#issuecomment-3410688605",
            "id": 3410688605,
            "issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/neovim/neovim/issues/36188",
