        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "> you previously argued that routing based on message kind is unpredictable, which prompted #35028\r\n\r\nThere are multiple axes at play.\r\n- The primary goal of https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/34281 is to not get \"stuck\" randomly in the pager for unpredictable cases.\r\n    - This PR sketch doesn't change that. The cursor should never, ever be stuck in the pager after any kind of message.\r\n- Then, beyond that, I suggested that we start by having one single behavior so that we can then tune things as they become obvious.\r\n    - It is now obvious that errors should never be displayed in full.\r\n- \"Shell output\" and such are still, from the user POV, rather ambiguous. Plugins may show output as \"shell output\" or \"echo output\". From the user POV it's random, so deciding when to show/not show those kinds feels \"random\".",
